==English==

{{rank|long|am|way|122|even|say|well|many}}

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/i:vən/}}
*{{audio|en-us-even.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology 1===
Old English [[efen]] (''adjective''), [[efnan]] (''verb'').

====Adjective====
{{en-ad|even}}

#<!--AdjFlat+Level-->Flat and level.
#:''Clear out those rocks.  The surface must be even.''
#<!--AdjWithoutVariation-->Without great variation.
#:''Despite her fear, she spoke in an even voice.''
# Equal in proportion, quantity, size etc.
#:''The distribution of food must be even.''
#<!--AdjDivisibleBy2-->{{arithmetic}} (''no comparative or superlative'') Leaving no remainder when divided by 2.
#: ''Four, fourteen and forty are even numbers.''

=====Synonyms=====
*<!--AdjFlat+Level-->(''flat and level''): [[flat]], [[level]], [[uniform]]
*<!--AdjWithoutVariation-->(''without great variation''): [[monotone]] (''voice'')

=====Antonyms=====
*<!--AdjFlat+Level-->(''flat and level''): [[uneven]]
*(''arithmetic''): [[odd]]

